# 📊 Customer Churn Prediction using Machine Learning

## 🚀 Project Overview
This project predicts whether a telecom customer will churn (leave the service) based on historical customer data using Machine Learning techniques.

The model is trained using the Telco Customer Churn dataset and uses a Random Forest classifier for prediction.

---

## 🧠 Problem Statement
Telecom companies face customer loss (churn), which impacts revenue. This project helps identify customers likely to churn so that companies can take preventive actions.

---

## ⚙️ Tech Stack
- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Scikit-learn

---

## 📊 Dataset
Used IBM Telco Customer Churn dataset containing:
- Customer demographics
- Service usage details
- Billing information
- Churn status (Yes/No)

---

## 🧪 Machine Learning Model
- Random Forest Classifier
- Label Encoding for categorical features
- Train-test split (80/20)

---

## 📈 Workflow
1. Load dataset  
2. Data cleaning  
3. Encode categorical variables  
4. Train model  
5. Evaluate accuracy  
6. Predict churn  

---

## ▶️ How to Run

```bash
pip install pandas numpy scikit-learn

python model.py[0].values))